Job Title: MiL dSPAVE Integration Lab Validation Engineer (Mining OT Vendor)
Ad Text:
A global leader of mining equipment and mining operational technologies has a challenging and rewarding contract HiL dSPACE Integration Lab Validation Engineer role. You'll join their Global Validation team and play a crucial role in delivering high-quality Mining Operation Technology for underground mines. You'll work with cutting-edge technology that enables autonomous machine operations, production recording management and monitoring in underground mining applications.

The position offers continuous learning opportunities in innovative technology, chances to mentor team members and the ability to expand your professional network in a dynamic industry.

Key Responsibilities:

Collaborate with the Underground Technology Global Validation Team & stakeholders on schedule, process & quality goals
Develop test plans for Model in the Loop system validation of software releases & new features
Maintain & expand Test Plan & Test Case libraries
Execute Test Cases including operation of simulated underground mining machines & autonomy systems
Identify & analyse software & system issues, assigning corrective action tasks & developing emergency containment when necessary
Partner with subsystem teams to implement interim & permanent solutions
Document, track & manage issues
Install & validate on/off machine hardware systems in lab environments
Support on-machine validation of technology products at the Proving Ground in Tasmania
Troubleshoot software & comms issues on machines
Collect data using development tools for offline analysis
Contribute to system requirements definition for functionality & features
Qualifications

Required:

Bachelor’s degree (or equivalent experience) in an accredited Engineering or Computer Science curriculum
3+ years of relevant work experience
Strong analytical skills
Hardware in the Loop system or Model in the Loop validation experience using dSPACE
Desired:

Good communication, interpersonal and collaboration skills.
Experience with Linux
Networking and radio communication experience
Experience with on-machine validation or systems (can be gained on the job)
Experience with Caterpillar development tools (can be gained on the job)
Experience of datalink analysis
Join the Team

Be part of a forward-thinking team that's shaping the future of underground mining technology.

The initial duration is 12 months and but the role will be on-going for strong performers.

The role is based at Tullamarine and you'll be required to work in the office 5 days per week. This organisation offers flexible work hours.

You must possess Australian/NZ citizenship or Australian PR to be considered for this role.

For further details, contact Fortunato (Forty) Galluzzo on 043 870 9417 or alternately email on forty@taskgroup.com.au.

AI Automation Specialist / Automation Engineer

Location: Australia (Remote / Hybrid)

Type: Full-Time or Contract (flexible)

Salary: Competitive, based on experience

About the Role

We’re looking for an AI Automation Specialist to help design and build intelligent automations that remove manual work, connect systems, and scale how our business operates.

This role sits at the intersection of automation, AI, and operations. You’ll work with modern automation tools and AI models to create workflows and agents that support real business outcomes - not experiments or demos.

You don’t need to be wedded to one platform. What matters is your ability to understand a problem, design a system, and automate it reliably.

⸻

What You’ll Do

    •    Identify manual or repetitive processes and turn them into smart automations

    •    Design and build workflows using tools such as:

    •    n8n, Make, Zapier, or similar

    •    Custom scripts or lightweight services where needed

    •    Build and integrate AI-powered workflows and agents, including:

    •    Content processing and transformation

    •    Decision-making and routing

    •    Data enrichment and validation

    •    Connect and integrate systems via APIs, webhooks, and third-party platforms

    •    Ensure automations are production-ready, with proper error handling, logging, and documentation

    •    Continuously improve existing workflows as the business scales

    •    Collaborate with leadership and teams to prioritise and deliver high-impact automation

⸻

What We’re Looking For

Essential

    •    Experience building automation workflows in real-world environments

    •    Comfortable working across multiple tools and platforms

    •    Strong understanding of APIs, data flows, and system integration

    •    Exposure to AI tools and large language models (LLMs)

    •    Logical, structured thinker who enjoys solving operational problems

    •    Able to work independently and own solutions end-to-end

Nice to Have

    •    Experience with AI agents or LLM orchestration

    •    Light coding experience (JavaScript, Python, or similar)

    •    Experience with no-code / low-code automation platforms

    •    Background in operations, product, or technical consulting

⸻

What Success Looks Like

    •    Manual processes are automated and no longer bottlenecks

    •    Systems talk to each other cleanly and reliably

    •    AI is used thoughtfully to augment workflows (not as a gimmick)

    •    Teams save time and trust the automations you’ve built

    •    Clear documentation means systems are easy to maintain and evolve

⸻

Why Join Us

    •    Work on meaningful, real-world automation problems

    •    Direct access to decision-makers and fast iteration

    •    Freedom to choose the right tools for the job

    •    Opportunity to shape how AI and automation are used across the business

    •    Flexible working arrangements

⸻

How to Apply

Please include:

    •    A brief overview of your automation experience

    •    Examples of workflows, automations, or systems you’ve built (links, screenshots, or descriptions)

    •    Any experience working with AI-driven workflows or agents

About the Company

We are an established systems integration contractor offering industrial automation and consulting services across a wide variety of industries.

Our mission is to help local manufacturing and processing businesses to be as successful as they possibly can be through skillful application of the latest control system technologies. Our customers include large well-known brands, as well as emerging businesses bringing exciting new products to the market.

Clients throughout Australia have been so thrilled with our practical and innovative approach to automating their processes and boosting their efficiency that demand for our services is at an all-time high. We therefore need to expand our incredible team of technology innovators with more skilled individuals who are seeking to make a real difference.

About the Role

We are looking for versatile engineers with real-world experience in machine control systems, especially industrial software platforms like Siemens, Rockwell, Phoenix and others.

The role has a fantastic amount of variety both in the technologies you'll deal with and the applications you'll encounter. Our wide cross-section of customers will provide you with opportunity to learn about many different industrial manufacturing processes for everything from food and beverage to steel tube forming, timber milling to concrete batching, textile weaving to material packaging, standalone machines to entire lines.

You will play a vital role across all stages of the job lifecycle. A typical week will consist of a mix of project work (typically 1-3 projects running concurrently), an occasional spot of troubleshooting for a breakdown at a customer site, some time assisting other team members, and always honing your skills through regular professional development and learning.

On average approximately half of your time will be spent in the office on system design and program preparation, and half out on sites commissioning and tuning your systems. Some working-from-home is available, and a small amount of regional and interstate travel is involved from time to time.

Supported by great colleagues you will carry out tasks such as:

Scoping and investigating requirements for new projects,

Advising and guiding customers in their choice of technologies and system architectures.

Designing, developing and commissioning PLC code and HMI interfaces

Programming inverters for induction motors and servo drive motion controls

Creating execution sequences for pneumatic and hydraulic actuators

Installing and configuring all manner of instrumentation sensors

Implementing safety access controls and interlocks

Industrial networking (both TCP/IP and serial-based field buses)

Planning and monitoring project phases

Mentoring less experienced staff

Providing advice to installation teams,

Troubleshooting and problem solving.

About the Person

You will have an engineering or programming degree, and at least 3 years working in industry, with hands-on experience programming PLCs, HMIs, servos drives and related devices to successfully automate production processes. You will also have exceptional verbal and written English communication skills which are crucial to this role where you will be interacting with a wide variety of people from production managers to factory line workers.

Candidates must be Australian citizens or permanent residents.

Maybe you've had a series of contracts and are now looking for a permanent role with more responsibility. Perhaps you've been supporting one particular business or line and are now yearning for some more variety. Or maybe you're already a seasoned automation professional looking for your next challenge.

Whatever your journey, we'd love you to take the next step here at Integrelec.

If this sounds like the role for you, then please submit your resume, and it will be advantageous to also call our office on (07) 3123 9538 to introduce yourself.

Shape how a member-owned bank uses data and AI to do the right thing at scale
Highly reputable and trusted brand and Employer of Choice for Gender Equality
Competitive salary package on offer to attract the very best 

We are now seeking a Head of Data & AI to lead strategy, governance and delivery, turning data into trusted insights and responsible AI into real business and member outcomes.

About the role

Reporting to the Chief Digital Officer, this role is about building foundations that last, not running one-off programs. You will shape how data and AI are prioritised, governed and delivered across the bank, working closely with Technology, Digital, Transformation, Business leaders and the Executive Data & AI Committee.

You’ll balance ambition with pragmatism, delivering value incrementally while embedding strong risk, privacy and ethical guardrails in line with APRA and Australian regulatory expectations.

A clear, enterprise-wide data and AI strategy aligned to IMB’s business priorities and member outcomes
Prioritisation of high-value use cases across customer insights, risk, operations and decision-making
Embedded governance across the full lifecycle  from idea to production to retirement
Sustainable in-house capability, supported by partners where appropriate
A multidisciplinary team of data engineers, analysts, scientists and architects
A modern data and analytics ecosystem across AWS, Microsoft (including Power BI/Azure) and IBM DataStage

What you’ll bring

Senior leadership experience building data, analytics and AI capabilities within financial services or regulated environments
Strong technical grounding across cloud platforms, data engineering, analytics and machine learning
Deep understanding of data risk, privacy and AI governance, with the confidence to advise executives on trade-offs and investment decisions
A collaborative, pragmatic leadership style — able to influence, simplify and deliver
A commitment to ethical, responsible and transparent use of data and AI

Why IMB?

IMB Bank is a leading customer-owned bank offering a full range of products and services in both retail and business banking. Our purpose is to provide simple, competitive, and authentic banking to help our customers and communities be better off and we’ve doing that for over 145 years. An award-winning and growing organisation, we’ve donated more than $13 million through our Community Foundation to over 1100 projects in our communities.   

IMB benefits include:

Great training and onboarding 
Genuine career pathways and opportunity to accelerate your skills and experience
A supportive culture that actively promotes diversity and inclusion and the wellbeing of our employees 
Designated wellbeing days
Friendly and professional team environment
Product concessions
Purchased leave options

Apply now by visiting imbcareers.com.au and follow the prompts. Application close date 27th February 2026.

Job Title: AI/ML Consultant, Professional Services, Google Cloud
Ad Text:
At Google, we have a vision of empowerment and equitable opportunity for all Aboriginal and Torres Strait Islander peoples and commit to building reconciliation through Google’s technology, platforms and people and we welcome Indigenous applicants. Please see our Reconciliation Action Plan for more information.

Minimum qualifications:

Bachelor's degree or equivalent practical experience.
5 years of experience in managing project and delivering technical solutions.
Experience in one or more discipline areas: machine learning, recommendation systems, natural language processing, computer vision, pattern recognition, or artificial intelligence.

Experience with technical client service (e.g., consulting experience).
Preferred qualifications:

Experience in systems design with ability to architect and explain data analytics pipelines and data flows.

Experience designing and deploying with one or more from the following technologies: TensorFlow, Spark ML, CNTK, Torch, Caffe, Scikit-learn.

Experience building cloud-based conversational AI solutions.
Experience with generative AI products, technologies, or infrastructure.
Experience in a statistical programming language like R or Python and applied machine learning techniques (e.g., dimensionality reduction strategies, classification, and natural language processing frameworks).
Excellent communication, written, presentation and problem-solving skills.
About the job
The Google Cloud Consulting Professional Services team guides customers through the moments that matter most in their cloud journey to help businesses thrive. We help customers transform and evolve their business through the use of Google’s global network, web-scale data centers, and software infrastructure. As part of an innovative team in this rapidly growing business, you will help shape the future of businesses of all sizes and use technology to connect with customers, employees, and partners.

As an Artificial Intelligence/Machine Learning (AI/ML) Consultant, you will work directly with Google’s most customers on critical projects to help them transform their businesses using AI/ML technologies. You will help our customers to develop, deploy, and manage custom AI solutions in production using Google Cloud technologies. You will provide technical project management, consulting and technical aptitude to customer engagements while working with client executives and key technical leaders to deploy solutions on Google Cloud Platform. You will also work closely with key Google partners currently servicing accounts to scope engagements, manage programs, deliver consulting services, and provide technical guidance and best practice expertise. You will possess a background in developing AI solutions, applying key industry tools, techniques, and methodologies. You will know how to navigate ambiguity, and you will be a technical expert in your field, and you can deliver customer success. You will have excellent client-facing communication and project management skills.Google Cloud accelerates every organization’s ability to digitally transform its business and industry. We deliver enterprise-grade solutions that leverage Google’s cutting-edge technology, and tools that help developers build more sustainably. Customers in more than 200 countries and territories turn to Google Cloud as their trusted partner to enable growth and solve their most critical business problems.

Responsibilities

Work with customer technical leads, client executives, and partners to scope, manage and deliver successful implementations of Cloud AI solutions, becoming a trusted advisor to decision makers throughout the engagement.
Propose solution architectures and manage the deployment of cloud based machine learning solutions according to customer requirements and implementation best practices.
Work with internal specialists, Product, and Engineering teams to package approaches, best practices, and lessons learned into thought leadership, methodologies, and published assets.
Interact with Sales, Partners, and customer technical stakeholders to manage project scope, priorities, deliverables, risks and issues, and timelines for successful client outcomes.
Travel approximately 30% of the time for client engagements.
Google is proud to be an equal opportunity workplace and is an affirmative action employer. We are committed to equal employment opportunity regardless of race, color, ancestry, religion, sex, national origin, sexual orientation, age, citizenship, marital status, disability, gender identity or Veteran status. We also consider qualified applicants regardless of criminal histories, consistent with legal requirements. See also Google's EEO Policy and EEO is the Law.
